Someone is fixing my kitchen floor right now. And I'm pretending to have a job and work from home while I'm actually watching Too Hot to Handle.
If only I could open the file for crying out loud. (Damn OneDrive.)
Voice of a Hacker: I'm in.
And that's exactly where he starts drilling very loudly. Hurray.
It feels uncomfortable to turn my air purifier to the max when I can smell wood dust, but I'd be fine even if it's not a mask-wearer's enemy. And do I really need to protect myself?
I would really like to go to bed again, but I can't until he leaves.
At least I have finally finished revising Chapter 4.
Chapter five is long, but it's so damn terrifying. Oh yes, that's the good stuff!
I'm searching and replacing for … ➡️ Ellipsis Symbol and there are 54 in this chapter 😊
But no, I'm sticking to that. Natural language is usually staccato, especially when one becomes emotional.
The handyman is now using the vacuum cleaner. Hopefully that means he'll be finished soon.
He went out to cut something (at least that's what it sounds like). I just looked in on him secretly, to see how far he's gotten. There's still a lot to do :(
Still 7 pages in Chapter 5. It's still my favorite chapter and it's pretty tidy – mainly changes to the font and very small corrections to direct speech and I still have to rephrase everything a bit more concisely. But I could really use a break and a cup of tea right now, but the guy is still in my kitchen.
Now he has just started vacuuming again. Hopefully, that's a good sign.
The kitchen type is gone!
He told me that he had made an estimate for the entire floor, but the landlords were too stingy and only paid for the part next to the door that's no longer in order. It feels just as good.
The house is being ventilated and in the kitchen my air purifier is running, while I am drinking tea in the garden!
